<br>
Case and point: OS group, bar chef, consisting of:<br>
58 sk<br>
55/56 pally<br>
53 monk<br>
60 chanter<br>
54 shaman<br>
51 cleric<br>
<br>
The cleric did NOT have remedy.  Therefore, he was overhealing with Superior, and his buffs really took alot of mana out of his pool.  As the shaman, I had to keep a close eye on the healing situation in the camp.<br>
<br>
In the 3 or 4 hours that we were moving down to, camping, and moving up from bar / chef, I witnessed the following:<br>
<br>
1.  The SK taking roughly 80% of the damage<br>
2.  The Enc taking roughly 10% of the damage<br>
3.  The Shaman taking roughly 10% of the damage<br>
<br>
The cleric, monk, and pally in total took between 0-10% of the damage.<br>
<br>
We were on a master loot system.  Before the trinket split (any cash gems and rings / necklaces) I asked the cleric what his peridot cost was.  In this case, the cleric (Supreem) refused to take cash off the top.  I tried insisting three or four times that he give me a total, but he refused.  Had he told me, I would have given him trinkets IN ADDITION to the normal split, but by taking his cost off the top it adjusts the group share accordingly.  <br>
<br>
Common sense dictates that if you aren't getting hit, you DON'T NEED SYMBOL.  Yet, the monk and pally both asked for symbol with less than an hour left in the hunt because they felt &quot;safer&quot; with it.  That affects the group bottom line as well.<br>
<br>
This isn't that tough.  How many costs are you dealing with?<br>
<br>
Peridots cost between 10-14pp<br>
Fire opals sell for around 45pp<br>
Star rubies sell for around 60pp<br>
Rubies sell for around 110pp<br>
Emerald rings sell for around 80pp<br>
Mythral amulets sell for around 110pp<br>
Sapphires sell for around 95pp<br>
Sapphire necklaces sell for around 160pp<br>
<br>
Worried about your charisma?  What shaman or enchanter wouldn't donate a CHA buff to the cleric to help him out?  None that I know and work with.<br>
<br>
Granted, we are turning a fun game into something accountants would rather play, but if you want to be absolutely fair, this is one of the ways you can do it.  The whole system falls apart if the master looter skims, or if the cleric inflates his peridot cost, or if people start complaining that their personal buffs cost components as well.  This is a GROUP situation, and if your buffs are helping out group members (rune DOES fall into this, manaskin does NOT), you should be reimbursed accordingly. <p>Tanuden <BR>
54 Shaman, EMarr<BR>
Husband to Lady Oriania of UPS<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uislington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Islington</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/30/01 5:41:02 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.inyiensmagicalrealm.com/images/Islington.jpg width=200 height=350></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics-Peridots and You (open discussion)</span><hr size=1> This thread is really sad and it shows the true character of all these new characters who were able to powerlevel themselves to 50 in two months.  It NEVER used to be this way with people complaining about gems going to the Cleric.  It was common practice and very accepted.  When I played my Paladin and would Master Loot, if a gem dropped I diddn’t even think twice before handing it straight to the Cleric.  Now it seems that people can fly to 50 utilizing 6 zones, none of which have good coin, fine steel, or decent drops but where experience flys by at an insane rate.  People are entering the high level game earlier with less money and gear then in the days of old.<br>
<br>
Now that I am a Cleric, I understand why this is done.  OS is a strange zone in which gem drops are fairly common.  On a good night, a Cleric will get a profit.  However most of the other level 45 – 60 dungeons/zones do not drop cash loot in nearly the same quantity.  Over the past week I used up 800pp in Peridots in various places (Karnors Castle, Chardok and the Hole) AFTER taking into consideration the few cash drops that were defaulted to me.  On Sunday I went to OS and had an amazing group.  I walked out of there with 1.2k in cash loot and used about 300pp in Peridots.  If you look at that one group, I came out ahead by 900pp.  If you look at the week as a whole, I came out ahead 100pp (which is a bit less than the other group mates since I made sure that each one got at least 1 or 2 good cash loots).<br>
<br>
OS is gem heaven and many Clerics view it as a place to resupply their Peridot bags.  It’s one of the few zones that we can come out ahead in and help to balance all of the other zones where we lose big.  Most Clerics are not going in with malicious intent to screw people over; they’re simply trying to balance their losses.<br>
<br>
Personally I’m still trying to find a balance on gems/peridots.  When I start in OS or any tougher exp camp that we have to break ourselves, I will symbol everyone.  Once we are at the camp and have things under control, the following get a Symbol: Myself (for timing purposes and the fact that on a bad pull I can draw some nasty aggro), the Puller, the Main Tank, and the Enchanter.  After that if someone asks me for a Symbol, I’ll give it to you but you’re not a priority if mana is tight.  I am now keeping track of gem prices just to keep an idea as to where I’m at (I’m an Accountant alright?) in a given camp.  Ideally I want to come out ahead on cash loot while passing each member of the group a couple of gems.  One of the things I try to do is keep the first 3 gem drops and then pass out every other gem that drops after those 3 (3 gems drop and I keep, the 4th gem is randomed, the 5th is mine, the 6th is randomed etc).  It seems to be a good system where I cover my expenses and everyone else walks away with some gems.<br>
<br>
Now as to other classes that use Peridots for personal spells, to me that seems a personal choice.  If you are burning through dots for shielding spells, you are doing something wrong.  I understand totally that as a Wizard you will overburn every now and then but if you are constantly getting aggro and burning through your shield, you’re doing something wrong.<br>
<br>
For the Necro complaining about Coffin Costs, you do NOT have to absorb the cost yourself.  When I get into a situation where corpse summoning becomes necessary, you better believe I’m going to foot the bill to have my corpse returned to me.  There is no way I would ever ask a Necromancer to summon my Corpse without covering the cost of the Coffin and a bit extra for the mana/trouble.<br>
<br>
Also, I would advise everyone out there to put together a Charisma kit.  With my Charisma kit, I can hit 110 CHR and the whole kit cost me 100pp.  I have made that back many times over when using it to get the best prices on things.<br>
 <p>Islington Angelwatch<br>
Cavalier of 53 seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<br>
Qustil Angelwatch<br>
Vicar of 52 seasons in the service to the Great Mother, Tunare <br>
