<br>
I've been playing other charectors lately and have noticed that I can play for weeks at a time without having any out of pocket expense to play, except for the peridots that I've taken to carrying and handing to the clerics before asking for a symbol.<br>
<br>
There have been some well thought out reponses to this thread and I can see the point of view on most of them, but not being able to remember to bring food/water/arrows to a dungeon isn't a good excuse to me. Thats part of staying alive at the most rudimentary level.<br>
<br>
Want manaskin? Bring a peridot<br>
Want rune? Bring a peridot<br>
Want a 60 pet? Bring a peridot<br>
Want a symbol? Bring a peridot<br>
<br>
In doing this all loot (read not just OS gems) can be split fairly to all in the group without anyone feeling shortchanged or cheated.<br>
<br>
Its the fairest way I could come up with, or we can leave it as it stands which is what will probably happen anyways.  I'm open to any other ideas that may be better than the one I've proposed.<br>
<br>
Treage Shadowbane (&lt;------keeps 100 peridots in stock)<br>
