And I don't know what other people think flying through levels is but it's taken me a over a year to get to 50.<br>
I don't think we should fight over who gets the gems, but we should all get an equal chance at the gems we NEED.  The only time I have ever asked to get or random between me and the cleric is if it's peridot, an emerald, or a star ruby.  Otherwise looting is whatever the group has set up.  I think they should get any other gems because they are buffing the tanks.  But it is not right that they should get everything regardless of who needs it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulanidormoonsinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lanidor Moonsinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/30/01 11:48:23 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/tsatwood/stuff.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Clerics-Peridots and You (open discussion)</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, it is not the pick-up group's responsibility to ensure that I'm compensated for being down on cash and/or peridots from past groups.  If there's enough cash loot to cover my peridot expense for a particular group, then I split the rest with the group evenly (or as close as possible).  If the enchie has been runing, then I give him/her a good deal more than the others.  <br>
<br>
Usually I get caught up by doing a res or two here and there...I don't ask for donations, but I do accept them to help with these sort of expenses.  I have my epic, so I don't sweat the mana, and if I do get a donation, well...I end up doing Naltron or Marzin on the one who donated.  Am I broke most of the time?  Yep.  Do I care?  Nope.  Do I get pissed when I hear about a cleric who sits in OS Jail for 8 or 10 hours and keeps every single gem?  Goddamn right.  <br>
<br>
But to address the initial question...how are you gonna get players to bring peridots (yes, I carry pearls, batwings, and fishscales, too) when half of them forget to even bring food!  *grin*  Don't bring your peridots, folks, cuz more often than not, some well-meaning idiot will try to trade me a peridot in the middle of a fight when I need to see just how badly the enchie is getting bent over and reamed by a coupla froggies.  <br>
