 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujlaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jlaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/01 12:44:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Clerics-Peridots and You (open discussion)</span><hr size=1> Just a partial solution for those of you grinding away the XP in Sebillis, Velks, whatever.<br>
<br>
Don't Symbol the warrior.<br>
<br>
I'm a warrior, not a great one STA wise.  I always have plenty of HP.  Symbol is nice, but I'd say that now, 75 percent of the time I am healed by a Celestial healing, or whatever Heal over Time spell.  The extra HP don't make a big difference unless you are CHealing (For efficiency or whatever).  It's not as if a decent group should have mana problems, right?<br>
<br>
I think the Tank/Puller needs to be Symboled during the break-in and in some camps where pulling 3-4 mobs is a regular thing, but once a spawn is broken, there isn't much reason to keep symbol up.  At most will be 2 adds unless your puller is really pulling crazy.  Any tank worth his salt can tank 3 of anything a pickup group in Seb is doing for long enough for a Mez or a Cheal to go off.<br>
<br>
And stop buffing secondary tanks, and other classes that shouldn't get aggroed.  Symboling them just encourages sloppy play (including the wizard).  The cleric and ench need a symbol at all times, IMO that's about it.  Symbol the group on breakin and then just those 2.  Would save you guys a lot of Peridots.<br>
<br>
Oh, but still, go ahead and keep every gem.  I have no quibble with clerics getting those gems.  And if they make a small profit that day, fine.  I guarantee that cleric will be screwed over another day and need the money. <br>
<br>
And if there's a Shaman in the group, that Talisman Spell is Component-Free, a Stamina buff adds a few more hp, have your ranger/pally buff the others and that should be plenty of HP to stay alive in a Pickup situation.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cents<br>
<br>
Jlaen Gaidin<br>
